DESCRIPTION:Who gets to decide who we really are? Why does society dictate 
 our identity? Two Strangers and a Clipboard is a new comedy-drama that drop
 s audiences into a world almost like ours. Except your identity is assigned
  by the day you’re born. When Sam and Gary\, two strangers with nothing i
 n common\, find themselves in a court waiting room\, a single tick on a cli
 pboard could change the course of their lives. March 2026 preview was sold 
 out with 4 star reviews\, written by the writer of last year's Camden Fring
 e sell-out 5-star reviewed Maybe You Should Know.\nMore info: https://comed
 yatlas.app/comedy-atlas/event/two-strangers-and-a-clipboard/
